==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Separator
<hw>Sep"a*ra`tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.]</ety>
<def>One who, or that which, separates.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd>
<fld>(Steam Boilers)</fld> <def>A device for depriving steam of
particles of water mixed with it.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Mining)</fld>
<def>An apparatus for sorting pulverized ores into grades, or separating
them from gangue.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <fld>(Weaving)</fld> <def>An
instrument used for spreading apart the threads of the warp in the loom,
etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Separatory</ent>⟦br⟧
